}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://wpml.org/?p=1046119";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:341:"Building a fully multilingual real estate site can be challenging. In this post, we teach how you can do it using Toolset plugins. You can start from scratch, or by using a complete reference design to speed up development. What our multilingual real estate site will include &#8220;Real estate&#8221; is anything that you build on [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Amir";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17387:"<p><strong>Building a fully multilingual real estate site can be challenging. In this post, we teach how you can do it using <a href="https://wp-types.com/">Toolset</a> plugins. You can start from scratch, or by using a complete reference design to speed up development.</strong></p>\n<h2>What our multilingual real estate site will include</h2>\n<p>&#8220;Real estate&#8221; is anything that you build on the ground, including just land (without anything built on it). Apartments, buildings, open land and offices have different fields and display differently. For this reason, we&#8217;ve decided to create a separate <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/create-a-custom-post-type/">custom post type</a> for each of them.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1046126" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600.jpg" alt="real-estate-home-600" width="600" height="623" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600.jpg 600w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600-144x150.jpg 144w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/real-estate-home-600-289x300.jpg 289w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>Each section in the site includes its own slider, with featured items and <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/front-page-filters/">custom search</a>. The custom search allows to find items according to their attributes (like size, price and features). It displays the results as a grid (textual list) and as markers on a Google Map.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1046155" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600.jpg" alt="custom-search-houses-600" width="600" height="781" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600.jpg 600w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600-115x150.jpg 115w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-houses-600-230x300.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>Each item displays with full details, including the listing agent, features and location on map.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1046171" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600.jpg" alt="single-house-600" width="600" height="606" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600.jpg 600w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600-297x300.jpg 297w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/single-house-600-90x90.jpg 90w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>So, if you&#8217;re going to build such a site yourself, you should:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create the custom post types and their fields and taxonomy</li>\n<li>Find how to implement a custom search (which is a major part of the project)</li>\n<li>Find how to display items on a Google Map</li>\n<li>Design how everything should display</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>How to build a multilingual real estate site with Toolset</h2>\n<p>There are great themes that will do this for you. Today, we will explain how to build such sites using our <a href="https://wp-types.com">Toolset</a> plugins.</p>\n<p>In case you haven&#8217;t heard about Toolset, it&#8217;s a package of plugins that help you build advanced sites with custom types, without programming. Toolset is a great fit for real estate sites because they rely heavily on custom post types and <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/using-custom-fields/">custom fields</a>. With Toolset, it&#8217;s easy to set up these custom types and fields and display them nicely on the front-end, without writing PHP.</p>\n<h3>Custom post types, fields and taxonomy for our real estate site</h3>\n<p>The first thing that we did was create the custom post types, custom fields and taxonomy. Even though the site looks simple, it has 7 different custom post types. Go to <strong>Toolset-&gt;Dashboard</strong> to create them.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046452" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046452" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-300x267.png" alt="The custom post types, fields and taxonomy for our real estate reference site" width="300" height="267" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-300x267.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-150x133.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-768x682.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site-1024x910.png 1024w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-types-for-real-estate-site.png 1129w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The custom post types, fields and taxonomy for our real estate reference site</p></div>\n<p>We created separate sets of custom fields, which add the attributes that each custom post type needs.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046474" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046474" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments-300x272.png" alt="Custom fields for apartments" width="300" height="272" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments-300x272.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments-150x136.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/fields-for-appartments.png 537w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Custom fields for apartments</p></div>\n<h3>Designing the site&#8217;s front-end with Toolset</h3>\n<p>Our front-end design center with Toolset is <strong>Layouts</strong> plugin. Layouts allows to design the &#8220;wireframe&#8221; of your site with a drag-and-drop editor. Then, you build the details of each of the blocks using <strong>Views</strong> plugin.</p>\n<p>First, you design the layout. You will start with the parent layout, which includes the elements that appear on each page in the site.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046543" style="width: 277px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046543" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-267x300.png" alt="The master layout of site, including the header, footer and placeholder for child layouts" width="267" height="300" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-267x300.png 267w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-134x150.png 134w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout-768x862.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/parent-layout.png 836w" sizes="(max-width: 267px) 100vw, 267px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The master layout of site, including the header, footer and placeholder for child layouts</p></div>\n<p>Then, you proceed with the design of the layouts (wireframes) for different main pages. This is the layout for the &#8220;houses archive&#8221;, which is the search page for houses.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046517" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046517" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-300x294.png" alt="Houses archive layout (the &quot;wireframe&quot; for the list of houses)" width="300" height="294" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-300x294.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-150x147.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout-768x753.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/houses-layout.png 833w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Houses archive layout (the &#8220;wireframe&#8221; for the list of houses)</p></div>\n<p>Once you have the layouts ready, it&#8217;s time to dive into the different blocks and build them. You will do this with <strong>Views</strong>. A View loads content from the database and displays it. You can create Views for simple lists, sliders, custom searches, tables, grids and anything that you can think of.</p>\n<p>Building a View takes three steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Select what the View is for (simple list, custom search, paginated list, slider)</li>\n<li>Choose more options, depending on the kind of View that you&#8217;re creating</li>\n<li>Design the output using HTML and CSS</li>\n</ol>\n<div id="attachment_1046598" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046598" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection-300x148.png" alt="Setting up a View - 1. Choose which content to display" width="300" height="148" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection-300x148.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection-150x74.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-content-selection.png 702w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting up a View &#8211; 1. choose which content to display</p></div>\n<div id="attachment_1046610" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046610" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting-300x116.png" alt="Setting up a View - 2. Select options for that kind of View" width="300" height="116" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting-300x116.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting-150x58.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/custom-search-view-setting.png 685w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting up a View &#8211; 2. choose options for that kind of View</p></div>\n<div id="attachment_1046621" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046621" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor-300x183.png" alt="Setting up a View - 3. Design the output using HTML" width="300" height="183" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor-300x183.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor-150x91.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/view-html-editor.png 738w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Setting up a View &#8211; 3. Design the output using HTML</p></div>\n<p>You may have noticed that the HTML code above uses shortcodes. These shortcodes display fields. You don&#8217;t need to memorize shortcodes or their options. To include a field in the HTML, click on the <strong>Fields and Views</strong> button in the editor. Select the field, enter its options and you get the completed shortcode.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046801" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046801" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field-300x266.png" alt="Inserting a field" width="300" height="266" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field-300x266.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field-150x133.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/inserting-a-field.png 544w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Inserting a field</p></div>\n<p>This way, you can create your own custom layouts and inside them, build the site-elements that you need. If you can write HTML and CSS, you can achieve anything with Toolset, without writing PHP.</p>\n<h2>How to translate</h2>\n<p>One of the great things about Toolset is the seamless integration with WPML. Anything that you create with Toolset is trivial to translate with WPML.</p>\n<p>Toolset automatically registers all &#8220;strings&#8221; for translation.</p>\n<p>When you go to <strong>WPML-&gt;String translation</strong>, you will see string domains for each of the Views (and other Toolset elements) that you created. There will also be domains for the custom post types and fields.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046871" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046871" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-300x212.png" alt="Translating the strings in a View" width="300" height="212" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-300x212.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-150x106.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view-768x541.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/translating-view.png 912w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating the strings in a View</p></div>\n<p>Translating layouts is even easier. Go to <strong>WPML-&gt;Translation management</strong> and you will see <strong>Layouts</strong> appearing in the <strong>Translation dashboard</strong>.</p>\n<div id="attachment_1046903" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1046903" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-300x233.png" alt="Layouts to translate" width="300" height="233" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-300x233.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-150x117.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate-768x598.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/layouts-to-translate.png 825w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Layouts to translate</p></div>\n<p>Translating a layout is similar to translating posts. You will get a list of texts which appear in the layout and translate just them. You don&#8217;t need to recreate layouts separately per language.</p>\n<h2>Start from scratch or from a complete working reference site</h2>\n<p>With Toolset, you can create your own multilingual real estate sites completely from scratch. You can also use our complete <a href="http://discover-wp.com/site-types/bootstrap-estate/">real estate reference</a> site as a starting point. Since our reference site is completely built using Toolset plugins, you can modify anything in it. You can edit element, remove and add your own.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=pcBn16RoWw8:T8sQbbyn6kU:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/pcBn16RoWw8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/build-multilingual-real-estate-sites-toolset-wpml/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/build-multilingual-real-estate-sites-toolset-wpml/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Compatible Plugins – Aug 2016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/44o5i2gsD20/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/compatible-plugins-aug-2016-2/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 30 Aug 2016 11:53:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Compatibility";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://wpml.org/?p=1036842";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:333:"Today we are happy to announce a few compatible WPML plugins. The plugins are, Meta Box, Search Live, WordPress MU Domain Mapping If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here: Multilingual Ready Themes Multilingual Ready Plugins Also, if you’re a theme or [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3894:"<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-995848" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Compatible-Plugins-Header-300x90.png" alt="Compatible Plugins-Header" width="400" height="121" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Compatible-Plugins-Header-300x90.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Compatible-Plugins-Header-150x45.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Compatible-Plugins-Header.png 680w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /><br />\nToday we are happy to announce a few compatible WPML plugins.</p>\n<p>The plugins are, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/meta-box/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Meta Box</a>, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/search-live/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Search Live</a>, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">WordPress MU Domain Mapping</a></p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you’re a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process, we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin Multilingual Ready.</p>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Meta Box</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Meta Box plugin is a powerful, professional solution to create custom meta boxes and custom fields for WordPress websites.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/meta-box/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download Meta Box</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Search Live</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Search Live supplies integrated live search facilities and advanced search features.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/search-live/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download Search Live</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">WordPress MU Domain Mapping</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Map any blog/site on a WordPressMU or WordPress 3.X network to an external domain.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-mu-domain-mapping/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download WordPress MU Domain Mapping</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=44o5i2gsD20:qwIwdS2jpc8:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=44o5i2gsD20:qwIwdS2jpc8:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=44o5i2gsD20:qwIwdS2jpc8:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=44o5i2gsD20:qwIwdS2jpc8:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=44o5i2gsD20:qwIwdS2jpc8:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=44o5i2gsD20:qwIwdS2jpc8:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/44o5i2gsD20" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/compatible-plugins-aug-2016-2/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/compatible-plugins-aug-2016-2/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:45:"How to create and translate custom post types";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/lnC4SXsAQ0I/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/how-to-create-and-translate-custom-post-types/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 30 Aug 2016 10:06:55 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"https://wpml.org/?p=1013431";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:335:"Introduction In this article, we will explain what custom post types are. In addition, we will show you how to create custom post types and how they can help in organizing and adding your website content. We will also add custom fields using the Types plugin. Moreover, we will demonstrate translating custom post types using [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Mohamed Khafaja";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19795:"<p><img src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Create-and-translate-custom-post-types-1.png" alt="Create and translate custom post types" width="568" height="159" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1036770" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Create-and-translate-custom-post-types-1.png 568w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Create-and-translate-custom-post-types-1-150x42.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Create-and-translate-custom-post-types-1-300x84.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px" /></p>\n<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>In this article, we will explain what custom post types are. In addition, we will show you how to create custom post types and how they can help in organizing and adding your website content. We will also add custom fields using the Types plugin. Moreover, we will demonstrate translating custom post types using WPML.</p>\n<h2>What are “Custom Post Types”?</h2>\n<p>Pages, posts, attachments, revisions, and navigation menus are the default WordPress post types; but what does that even mean? To be more clear and specific we can refer to “Custom Post Types,” also known as <strong>CPT</strong> or “Custom Content Type.” For example, Pages are pieces of content of the post type “page”; similarly, Posts are pieces of content of the post type “post.”</p>\n<p>Let us say that you have a website that reviews games. You will probably want to add reviews for more than one game. All games share some information (metadata) like release date, genre, platform, system requirements, screenshots, etc. In this case, you will want to create a custom post of type “game” and add custom fields to include the metadata. Other examples of custom post types could be Portfolios, Testimonials, and Products.</p>\n<p>Once you have created the custom post type game, it will show up on your WordPress dashboard as a separate menu item. You can also use the default categories available or create custom taxonomies suitable for the content. In addition, you will have the opportunity to choose how the custom post type will be displayed on the front-end. Here, you can read more about <a href="https://codex.wordpress.org/Post_Types" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Post Types</a>.</p>\n<h2>Why should I use “Custom Post Types”?</h2>\n<p>The general idea behind using custom post types is to make adding and displaying some specific pieces of content with the same structure or format easier. There are many indications of when you should start using a custom post type:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>When you do not need these pieces of content to have a chronological hierarchy;</li>\n<li>Additional fields are needed to add more details about the post;</li>\n<li>You want to display your posts in a specific way on the front-end;</li>\n<li>More categories and tags are needed to classify the pieces of content.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Creating custom post types and custom taxonomies will make it easier for your users to browse and sort your custom posts. For example, games can be sorted and searched by ( genre, release date, etc).</p>\n<p>The CPTs allows you to have pretty permalinks as they will show the custom post type name and the post name. For example, the URL for a Game post will be https://mysite.com/game/game-name</p>\n<h2>How to create “Custom Post Types”?</h2>\n<p>It is easier to create Custom Post Types using a plugin; however, you can also add some code to your functions.php theme file to add a Custom Post Type and custom fields to the theme you are using.</p>\n<p>You can add the code below to the functions.php file of your theme to create a custom post type; in this example, we will create the post type game. <strong>Note that</strong> you can add this code to the end of the functions.php file.</p>\n<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate">add_action( ''init'', ''create_post_type'');\nfunction create_post_type() {\n	$labels = array(\n	''name''               =&gt; _x( ''Games'', ''general name of the post type'' ),\n    ''singular_name''      =&gt; _x( ''Game'', ''name for one object of this post type'' ),\n    ''add_new''            =&gt; _x( ''Add New'', ''game'' ),\n    ''add_new_item''       =&gt; __( ''Add New Game'' ),\n    ''edit_item''          =&gt; __( ''Edit Game'' ),\n    ''new_item''           =&gt; __( ''New Game'' ),\n    ''all_items''          =&gt; __( ''All Games'' ),\n    ''view_item''          =&gt; __( ''View Game'' ),\n    ''search_items''       =&gt; __( ''Search Game'' ),\n   );\n   $args = array(\n     ''labels'' =&gt;  $labels, // An array that defines the different labels assigned to the custom post type\n     ''public'' =&gt;  true, // To show the custom post type on the WordPress dashboard\n     ''supports'' =&gt;  array( ''title'', ''editor'', ''thumbnail'', ''excerpt'', ''comments'' ), // Adds support for comments, revesions, etc\n     ''has_archive'' =&gt;  true, //Enables the custom post type archive at http://mysite.com/post-type/\n     ''hierarchical'' =&gt;  true, //Enables the custom post type to have a hierarchy\n     ''rewrite'' =&gt; array( ''slug'' =&gt;  _x(''game'', ''URL slug'')), //To be able to translate the custom post slug using WPML\n);\nregister_post_type( ''game'', $args );\n}</pre>\n<p>Indeed, this is the “geeky” way to create custom post types. An easier method is to use a plugin such as <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/types/" target="_blank">Types</a>. It is a free plugin that will allow you to create your own CPTs, custom fields, and custom taxonomies, effortlessly. In addition, Types documentation provides clear and detailed instructions to <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/create-a-custom-post-type/" target="_blank">create your custom post type</a> in a few minutes. We will use it to add the <strong>custom fields</strong> to our custom post type <strong>Game</strong>. You can also check the full documentation of <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/using-custom-fields/" target="_blank">adding custom fields</a>.</p>\n<p>After you install and activate Types, a new menu item will show on your WordPress dashboard. Follow the instructions below to add our custom fields to the CPT <strong>Game</strong>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to <strong>Toolset -&gt; Add New Post Field Group</strong>.</li>\n<li>Click on the <strong>Add New Group</strong> button.</li>\n<li>Fill the <strong>Name</strong> field and click on the <strong>Save Field Group</strong> button.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1013861" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group.png" alt="Crerate custom field group" width="550" height="259" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group.png 1367w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group-150x71.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group-300x141.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group-768x361.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Crerate-custom-field-group-1024x482.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="4">\n<ol start="4">\n<li>Assign the post field group to the CPT <strong>Game</strong> by clicking on the <strong>Edit</strong> button found on the <strong>“Where to include this Field Group”</strong> section and choose <strong>Games</strong> as illustrated below:</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Assgin-field-group-to-custom-post-type-game.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1013914" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Assgin-field-group-to-custom-post-type-game.png" alt="Assgin field group to custom post type game" width="550" height="227" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Assgin-field-group-to-custom-post-type-game.png 919w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Assgin-field-group-to-custom-post-type-game-150x62.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Assgin-field-group-to-custom-post-type-game-300x124.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Assgin-field-group-to-custom-post-type-game-768x317.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="4">\n<ol start="4">\n<li>Click on the <strong>Add New Field</strong> button and choose the field type. For example, we will create the custom fields <strong>release date</strong> and <strong>genre</strong>. We will choose the field type <strong>Date</strong> for the <strong>release date</strong>. Finally, we will set the field options and click on the <strong>Save Field Group</strong> button.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Release-date-custom-field.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1013926" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Release-date-custom-field.png" alt="Release date custom field" width="550" height="494" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Release-date-custom-field.png 916w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Release-date-custom-field-150x135.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Release-date-custom-field-300x270.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Release-date-custom-field-768x690.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<ol start="4">\n<li>To create the <strong>genre</strong> custom field, click on the <strong>Add New Field</strong> button and choose the field type to be <strong>Single Line</strong>. Set the field options and click on the <strong>Save Field Group</strong> button.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Genre-custom-field.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1013950" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Genre-custom-field.png" alt="Genre custom field" width="550" height="423" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Genre-custom-field.png 947w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Genre-custom-field-150x115.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Genre-custom-field-300x231.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Genre-custom-field-768x590.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<p>This is how our CPT <strong>Game</strong> will look on the WordPress dashboard:</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1013962" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end.png" alt="CPT on the front-end" width="550" height="449" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end.png 1072w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end-150x123.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end-300x245.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end-768x628.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/CPT-on-the-front-end-1024x837.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<p>You can use the <a href="https://wp-types.com/home/views-create-elegant-displays-for-your-content/" target="_blank">Views</a> plugin to display the <strong>Games</strong> CPT on your front-end. Views documentation will provide you with the information you need to <a href="https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/view-templates/" target="_blank">create content templates</a> to display your custom content type they way you want. Here is an example of how the <strong>Games</strong> CPT will be displayed on the front-end using the Views plugin:</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Custom-post-type-front-end-example.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1013999" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Custom-post-type-front-end-example.png" alt="Custom post type front-end example" width="550" height="757" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Custom-post-type-front-end-example.png 563w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Custom-post-type-front-end-example-109x150.png 109w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Custom-post-type-front-end-example-218x300.png 218w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<h2>How to translate “Custom Post Types”?</h2>\n<p>With <a href="https://wpml.org/purchase/" target="_blank">WPML</a> you can translate the CPTs that come with your theme, CPTs that you have created using a plugin, and CPTs that you have coded as shown in this tutorial. To set the CPT (Game) that we have created for translation, you will need to install and activate WPML’s core plugin (sitepress multilingual cms) along with the Translation Management add-on.</p>\n<ol>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to WPML -&gt; Translation Management and click on the <strong>Multilingual Content Setup</strong> tab and scroll down to the <strong>Custom Posts</strong> section.</li>\n<li>Set the CPT <strong>Game</strong> to be translated.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-CPT-to-be-translatable.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1014021" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-CPT-to-be-translatable.png" alt="Set CPT to be translatable" width="550" height="289" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-CPT-to-be-translatable.png 835w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-CPT-to-be-translatable-150x79.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-CPT-to-be-translatable-300x157.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-CPT-to-be-translatable-768x403.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<ol>\n<ol>\n<li>Click on the <strong>Save</strong> button.</li>\n<li>Go to the <strong>Custom Field Translation</strong> section and set the custom field <strong>genre</strong> to <strong>translate</strong> and the <strong>release date</strong> to <strong>copy from original to translation</strong> since we don’t need to translate the date.</li>\n<li>Click on the <strong>Save</strong> button.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-custom-fields-to-be-translatable.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1014034" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-custom-fields-to-be-translatable.png" alt="Set custom fields to be translatable" width="550" height="185" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-custom-fields-to-be-translatable.png 837w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-custom-fields-to-be-translatable-150x50.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-custom-fields-to-be-translatable-300x101.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Set-custom-fields-to-be-translatable-768x258.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<ol>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to <strong>Games -&gt; All Games</strong>. Click on the <strong>+</strong> icon to add your translation.</li>\n</ol>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1014085" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game.png" alt="Translate Game" width="550" height="153" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game.png 1051w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game-150x42.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game-300x83.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game-768x213.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translate-Game-1024x284.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click on the <strong>Copy content from English</strong> button.</li>\n<li>Add your translated text and click on the <strong>Publish button</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1014096" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts.png" alt="Add your translated texts" width="550" height="359" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts.png 1345w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts-150x98.png 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts-300x196.png 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts-768x501.png 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Add-your-translated-texts-1024x668.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a></p>\n<p>Here is an example of how the translated CPT (Games) would look like on the front-end:<br />\n<a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translated-custom-post-type-front-end.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1014211 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translated-custom-post-type-front-end.png" alt="Translated custom post type front end" width="547" height="761" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translated-custom-post-type-front-end.png 547w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translated-custom-post-type-front-end-108x150.png 108w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Translated-custom-post-type-front-end-216x300.png 216w" sizes="(max-width: 547px) 100vw, 547px" /></a></p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Using CPTs makes it easier to manage your content. If you are running a multilingual website, you will want to translate your CPTs, custom field type, and custom taxonomies. WPML can translate all these elements efficiently.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=lnC4SXsAQ0I:7E2nlf2saws:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=lnC4SXsAQ0I:7E2nlf2saws:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=lnC4SXsAQ0I:7E2nlf2saws:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=lnC4SXsAQ0I:7E2nlf2saws:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=lnC4SXsAQ0I:7E2nlf2saws:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=lnC4SXsAQ0I:7E2nlf2saws:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/lnC4SXsAQ0I" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/how-to-create-and-translate-custom-post-types/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://wpml.org/2016/08/how-to-create-and-translate-custom-post-types/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/wpml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"rel";s:3:"hub";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/";}}s:8:"xml